data.title: David Lee, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: David Lee stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
David Lee - Points

David Lee scores a career high 37 points (2008)

On November 29, 2008, David Lee tied his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 37 points in New York's home win against Golden State, 138-125. He also had 21 rebounds, 2 assists, 3 steals and 1 block. He shot 16/28 from two, 0/1 from three, shooting at 55.2% from the field. He also shot 5/8 from the free-throw line.

David Lee - Rebounds

David Lee grabs a career high 22 rebounds (2013)

On February 22, 2013, David Lee set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 22 rebounds in Golden State's home win against San Antonio, 107-101. He also had 25 points, 1 assist, 1 steal.

David Lee - Assists

David Lee gives a career high 11 assists (2012)

On December 21, 2012, David Lee set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 11 assists in Golden State's home win against Charlotte, 115-100. He also had 23 points, 11 rebounds.

David Lee - Steals

David Lee has a career high 5 steals (2009)

On January 02, 2009, David Lee tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 5 steals in New York's home loss against Indiana, 103-105. He also had 26 points, 11 rebounds and 3 assists.

David Lee - Blocks

David Lee blocks a career high 4 shots (2006)

On March 29, 2006, David Lee tied his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 4 blocks in New York's home loss against Boston, 98-123. He also had 4 points, 4 rebounds and 2 assists.

David Lee - Efficiency

David Lee records a career high 54 efficiency rating (2010)

On April 02, 2010, David Lee set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 54 efficiency in New York's road loss against Golden State, 128-117. He also had 37 points, 20 rebounds and 10 assists.
